      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TERRELL BANNER (1) is a fast dog well performed over the sprint races. Was in the money last time (23.20) over 401m at this track in a Grade 5 but is better suited by this sharper distance. Goes very well at the journey winning five races. Yet to taste defeat from three runs out of this box. Expected to feature in the finish again. GO FORWARD KENNY (3) is better than last start when sixth (18.81) from Box 3 at this track over 320m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Leading chance. CASH DE ORO (4) was below best at her last start when 7th at this track following a third place finish (18.42) there two back. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. One of the better chances. FAITH IN CAEDEN (7) was prominent throughout when successful last start. That form reads well.",
